No, mine is paper.

24:35.921 --> 24:38.605
It looks like leather, doesn't it?

24:38.625 --> 24:40.167
This is some management material.

24:40.507 --> 24:52.324
Here's the two little poems that were in... Let's see... Two of the other was in Burton's magazine.

24:56.725 --> 24:58.007
Oh, here's what it says.

25:02.593 --> 25:06.659
Oh, this is in the hands of Chicago College.

25:06.679 --> 25:12.247
That's a whole manuscript.

25:12.267 --> 25:14.270
These columns are in Al-A-Rap, I think.

25:15.332 --> 25:16.053
Oh, where?

25:16.113 --> 25:17.354
In Al-A-Rap, I want to look at that.

25:17.374 --> 25:18.075
Another time, yeah.

25:19.277 --> 25:24.825
I saw the young night bright all day, when a burning blush came, or the

25:25.244 --> 25:27.387
And then the other one on the right is To the River.

25:27.627 --> 25:29.229
Okay, can we just put the titles again?

25:29.269 --> 25:34.835
This is in an album with the numeral 32, two with a line.

25:35.816 --> 25:38.139
I saw the All Night Bridal Days, the first line of that one.

25:38.980 --> 25:40.041
