26:10.779 --> 26:15.805
You know, I'm impressed that you're not afraid to take these things out and handle them.

26:15.825 --> 26:17.107
Well, I don't take them out.

26:17.988 --> 26:20.451
Well, I must tell you, because they are so fragile.

26:21.111 --> 26:22.453
And then...

26:23.767 --> 26:35.362
You might want me to say this too, but you do keep the stuff in the vault.

26:35.382 --> 26:37.084
I do, yes.

26:37.845 --> 26:43.012
I keep most of the rare stuff in the vault and get it out when needed.

26:44.193 --> 26:50.922
This is for Annie, which I think is one of his greatest poems.

26:53.197 --> 26:55.140
This handwriting was beautiful, wasn't it?

26:55.501 --> 26:57.043
Now, this has eight stanzas.

26:57.143 --> 27:00.930
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight.

27:01.210 --> 27:02.933
The actual poem has, I think, 16.

27:03.794 --> 27:05.958
But the history of this particular copy is known.

27:06.058 --> 27:08.422
Poe sent this poem to the publisher.

27:09.624 --> 27:14.332
And somewhere along the line, half of it was lost.

27:15.093 --> 27:19.440
And all the books on Poe acknowledge that there's only one complete copy.

27:19.825 --> 27:21.828
which I think is in the Philadelphia Free Library.

27:21.848 --> 27:24.872
We're all 18, but this is the best you can do now.

27:24.932 --> 27:26.094
It's all with left.

27:26.114 --> 27:29.018
That's what it represents.

27:29.038 --> 27:34.066
And then this was the manuscript I bought that might have been considered a pony.

27:34.807 --> 27:45.482
And what we did, it has little holes here, you see, where a thread went through to bind it.

27:45.502 --> 27:47.605
And this little crease here, which was also...

27:48.192 --> 27:56.683
And all the copies in the bird collection and other collections that have this all have that same crease and those same holes in the same place.

27:56.783 --> 27:57.724
That's a New York problem.

27:57.744 --> 27:58.345
Yeah, yeah.

27:58.865 --> 27:59.646
This is page 11.

27:59.747 --> 28:09.539
I think, I'm not sure how many pages there were, but it is also known in all the reference books, see, that Pope broke this up and gave pages away to different people.

28:09.579 --> 28:13.784
So that's why, why it's, you know, there's no complete copy.

28:13.804 --> 28:15.246
When I sat with Bill Scheide,

28:15.496 --> 28:18.459
in Princeton, and he took out his Gutenberg Bible.

28:18.479 --> 28:19.741
